  <titleInfo>
    <title>1846 Feb. 20, Carthage, Tennessee [to] Mr. [and] Mrs. Mc Nabb, Canada / Adam Fergusson</title>
  </titleInfo>
  <abstract>This is a letter from Adam Fergusson to Mr. and Mrs. Mc Nabb, dated February 20, 1846. Fergusson is writing because he has not heard from the Mc Nabbs in a while. Fergusson gives a glowing report of current economic conditions, owing them to James K. Polk's administration. He writes about seeing their son, Dugald C. and his uncle on their trip. Fergusson reports helping them financially on their promise of reimbursement. He writes that he has still not received any news or money from them. Fergusson asks Mc Nabb to repay him, and to reply to the letter immediately.</abstract>
